            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1978-04-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1978-04-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="241"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d241">
                <head>241. Memorandum From Acting Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_CWM_1"
                        >Christopher</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1"
                        >Carter</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d241fn1">Source: Carter Library, Plains File,
                        Subject File, Box 38, State Department Evening Reports, 4/78. Secret.
                            <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">Carter</persName> wrote “Warren J” in the
                        upper right-hand corner of the first page of the memorandum. <persName
                            corresp="#p_VCR_1">Vance</persName> was in Moscow April 19–23; <persName
                            corresp="#p_CWM_1">Christopher</persName> served as Acting Secretary in
                        his absence.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1978-04-21">April 21, 1978</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[Omitted here is material unrelated to Yemen.]</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">South Yemen</hi>. The Saudis have finally come around to your
                    view that it would be helpful if we restored diplomatic relations with South
                    Yemen. We are assessing the timing and tactics of doing so.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d241fn2">In the left-hand margin next to this point, <persName
                            corresp="#p_CJE_1">Carter</persName> wrote: “I’m glad we finally got
                        permission to carry out my ‘views.’”</note>
                </p>
                <p>[Omitted here is material unrelated to Yemen.]</p>
            </div>
        </body>
